    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I installed Neovim nightly via scoop: `scoop install versions/neovim-nightly`.\n\nRunning `:checkhealth` gives this information:\n\n```\nSystem Info ~\n- ⚠️ WARNING Build is outdated. Local: b23d00ce99, Latest: 1901832f26fa\n- Nvim version: `v0.12.0-dev-2468+gb23d00ce99` b23d00ce99\n- Operating system: Windows_NT 10.0.26200\n- Terminal: unknown\n- $TERM: unknown\n```\n\nThis is the same version as the [nightly release page](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/tag/nightly):\n\n```\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2468+gb23d00ce99\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1772148810\n```\n\nIt appears as though b23d00ce99 is the latest release, but here it says that 1901832f26fa is the latest version.\n\nDoes this qualify as a bug?",
